name: Kawasaki Ninja h2r
describe: Its Ninja H2R track-only variant is the fastest and most powerful production motorcycle on the market, producing a maximum of 310 horsepower (230 kW) and 326 horsepower (243 kW) with ram-air.

name: Kawasaki z1000
describe: The Kawasaki Z1000 is a four-cylinder motorcycle introduced in 2003 with streetfighter or standard styling. The Z1000 was first introduced in 1977 superseding the previous 903 cc capacity Z1/Z900.

name: Kawasaki Z900
describe: The Kawasaki Z900 is a standard motorcycle of the Kawasaki Z series made by Kawasaki since 2017. It replaced the Z800

name: KTM 390 Duke
describe: KTM 390 Duke is a street bike available at a starting price of Rs. 2,94,286 in India. It is available in only 1 variant and 2 colours. The KTM 390 Duke is powered by 373.27cc BS6 engine which develops a power of 42.9 bhp and a torque of 37 Nm.

name: KTM 125 Duke
describe: KTM 125 Duke is a street bike available at a starting price of Rs. 1,76,208 in India. It is available in only 1 variant and 2 colours. The KTM 125 Duke is powered by 124.7cc BS6 engine which develops a power of 14.3 bhp and a torque of 12 Nm

name: KTM RC 125
describe: KTM RC 125 is an introductory bike from RC series of Austrian bike manufacturer KTM. KTM is popular worldwide as a bike brand from a modern mature and trustworthy place.

name: Yamaha MT-15
describe: Yamaha MT-15 is a motorcycle manufactured by Yamaha since 2018. It based on the Yamaha YZF-R15, with 155cc water-cooled single-cylinder engine equipped with the mainframe and variable valve timing mechanism, the inverted front fork, etc.

name: Yamaha R15
describe: The total series of R15 is very popular around the world, as well as Bangladesh. In continuation of this, Yamaha brought a new version of R15 to the market which is Yamaha R15 v3 in 2017

name: Yamaha FZ-Fi V3
describe: The new FZ-FI model mounts an air-cooled 4-stroke 149cc SOHC, 2-valve, single-cylinder fuel-injected 'BLUE CORE' engine, and engine's settings were optimized
